#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3611(para) 
msgid "With this option set to false, user-created tables no longer have an OID column unless <command>WITH OIDS</command> is specified in <command>CREATE TABLE</command>. Though OIDs have existed in all releases of <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>, their use is limited because they are only four bytes long and the counter is shared across all installed databases. The preferred way of uniquely identifying rows is via sequences and the <type>SERIAL</type> type, which have been supported since <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 6.4."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3624(para) 
msgid "Add <literal>E''</literal> syntax so eventually ordinary strings can treat backslashes literally (Bruce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3628(para) 
msgid "Currently <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> processes a backslash in a string literal as introducing a special escape sequence, e.g. <literal>\\n</literal> or <literal>\\010</literal>. While this allows easy entry of special values, it is nonstandard and makes porting of applications from other databases more difficult. For this reason, the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> project is planning to remove the special meaning of backslashes in strings. For backward compatibility and for users who want special backslash processing, a new string syntax has been created. This new string syntax is formed by writing an <literal>E</literal> immediately preceding the single quote that starts the string, e.g. <literal>E'hi\\n'</literal>. While this release does not change the handling of backslashes in strings, it does add new configuration parameters to help users migrate applications for future releases:"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3648(para) 
msgid "<varname>standard_conforming_strings</varname> — does this release treat backslashes literally in ordinary strings?"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3655(para) 
msgid "<varname>escape_string_warning</varname> — warn about backslashes in ordinary (non-E) strings"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3663(para) 
msgid "The <varname>standard_conforming_strings</varname> value is read-only. Applications can retrieve the value to know how backslashes are processed. (Presence of the parameter can also be taken as an indication that <literal>E''</literal> string syntax is supported.) In a future release, <varname>standard_conforming_strings</varname> will be true, meaning backslashes will be treated literally in non-E strings. To prepare for this change, use <literal>E''</literal> strings in places that need special backslash processing, and turn on <varname>escape_string_warning</varname> to find additional strings that need to be converted to use <literal>E''</literal>. Also, use two single-quotes (<literal>''</literal>) to embed a literal single-quote in a string, rather than the <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>-supported syntax of backslash single-quote (<literal>\\'</literal>). The former is standards-conforming and does not require the use of the <literal>E''</literal> string syntax. You can also use the <literal>$$</literal> string syntax, which does not treat backslashes specially."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3686(para) 
msgid "Make <command>REINDEX DATABASE</command> reindex all indexes in the database (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3690(para) 
msgid "Formerly, <command>REINDEX DATABASE</command> reindexed only system tables. This new behavior seems more intuitive. A new command <command>REINDEX SYSTEM</command> provides the old functionality of reindexing just the system tables."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3699(para) 
msgid "Read-only large object descriptors now obey MVCC snapshot semantics"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3702(para) 
msgid "When a large object is opened with <literal>INV_READ</literal> (and not <literal>INV_WRITE</literal>), the data read from the descriptor will now reflect a <quote>snapshot</quote> of the large object's state at the time of the transaction snapshot in use by the query that called <function>lo_open()</function>. To obtain the old behavior of always returning the latest committed data, include <literal>INV_WRITE</literal> in the mode flags for <function>lo_open()</function>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3714(para) 
msgid "Add proper dependencies for arguments of sequence functions (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3717(para) 
msgid "In previous releases, sequence names passed to <function>nextval()</function>, <function>currval()</function>, and <function>setval()</function> were stored as simple text strings, meaning that renaming or dropping a sequence used in a <literal>DEFAULT</literal> clause made the clause invalid. This release stores all newly-created sequence function arguments as internal OIDs, allowing them to track sequence renaming, and adding dependency information that prevents improper sequence removal. It also makes such <literal>DEFAULT</literal> clauses immune to schema renaming and search path changes."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3728(para) 
msgid "Some applications might rely on the old behavior of run-time lookup for sequence names. This can still be done by explicitly casting the argument to <type>text</type>, for example <literal>nextval('myseq'::text)</literal>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3740(programlisting) 
#, no-wrap
msgid "\nSELECT  'ALTER TABLE ' ||\n   pg_catalog.quote_ident(n.nspname) || '.' ||\n   pg_catalog.quote_ident(c.relname) ||\n   ' ALTER COLUMN ' || pg_catalog.quote_ident(a.attname) ||\n   ' SET DEFAULT ' ||\n   regexp_replace(d.adsrc,\n                  $$val\\(\\(('[^']*')::text\\)::regclass$$,\n                  $$val(\\1$$,\n                  'g') ||\n   ';'\nFROM    pg_namespace n, pg_class c, pg_attribute a, pg_attrdef d\nWHERE   n.oid = c.relnamespace AND\n   c.oid = a.attrelid AND\n   a.attrelid = d.adrelid AND\n   a.attnum = d.adnum AND\n   d.adsrc ~ $$val\\(\\('[^']*'::text\\)::regclass$$;\n"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3760(programlisting) 
#, no-wrap
msgid "\npsql -t -f fixseq.sql db1\n"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3766(programlisting) 
#, no-wrap
msgid "\npsql -t -f fixseq.sql db1 | psql -e db1\n"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3734(para) 
msgid "Pre-8.1 database dumps loaded into 8.1 will use the old text-based representation and therefore will not have the features of OID-stored arguments. However, it is possible to update a database containing text-based <literal>DEFAULT</literal> clauses. First, save this query into a file, such as <filename>fixseq.sql</filename>: <placeholder-1/> Next, run the query against a database to find what adjustments are required, like this for database <literal>db1</literal>: <placeholder-2/> This will show the <command>ALTER TABLE</command> commands needed to convert the database to the newer OID-based representation. If the commands look reasonable, run this to update the database: <placeholder-3/> This process must be repeated in each database to be updated."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3774(para) 
msgid "In <application>psql</application>, treat unquoted <literal>\\{digit}+</literal> sequences as octal (Bruce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3778(para) 
msgid "In previous releases, <literal>\\{digit}+</literal> sequences were treated as decimal, and only <literal>\\0{digit}+</literal> were treated as octal. This change was made for consistency."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3786(para) 
msgid "Remove grammar productions for prefix and postfix <literal>%</literal> and <literal>^</literal> operators (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3791(para) 
msgid "These have never been documented and complicated the use of the modulus operator (<literal>%</literal>) with negative numbers."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3798(para) 
msgid "Make <literal>&amp;&lt;</literal> and <literal>&amp;&gt;</literal> for polygons consistent with the box \"over\" operators (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3805(para) 
msgid "<command>CREATE LANGUAGE</command> can ignore the provided arguments in favor of information from <structname>pg_pltemplate</structname> (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3810(para) 
msgid "A new system catalog <structname>pg_pltemplate</structname> has been defined to carry information about the preferred definitions of procedural languages (such as whether they have validator functions). When an entry exists in this catalog for the language being created, <command>CREATE LANGUAGE</command> will ignore all its parameters except the language name and instead use the catalog information. This measure was taken because of increasing problems with obsolete language definitions being loaded by old dump files. As of 8.1, <application>pg_dump</application> will dump procedural language definitions as just <command>CREATE LANGUAGE <replaceable>name</replaceable></command>, relying on a template entry to exist at load time. We expect this will be a more future-proof representation."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3827(para) 
msgid "Make <function>pg_cancel_backend(int)</function> return a <type>boolean</type> rather than an <type>integer</type> (Neil)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3834(para) 
msgid "Some users are having problems loading UTF-8 data into 8.1.X. This is because previous versions allowed invalid UTF-8 byte sequences to be entered into the database, and this release properly accepts only valid UTF-8 sequences. One way to correct a dumpfile is to run the command <command>iconv -c -f UTF-8 -t UTF-8 -o cleanfile.sql dumpfile.sql</command>. The <literal>-c</literal> option removes invalid character sequences. A diff of the two files will show the sequences that are invalid. <command>iconv</command> reads the entire input file into memory so it might be necessary to use <application>split</application> to break up the dump into multiple smaller files for processing."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3853(title) 
msgid "Additional Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3855(para) 
msgid "Below you will find a detailed account of the additional changes between <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> 8.1 and the previous major release."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3862(title) 
msgid "Performance Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3866(para) 
msgid "Improve GiST and R-tree index performance (Neil)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3872(para) 
msgid "Improve the optimizer, including auto-resizing of hash joins (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3879(para) 
msgid "Overhaul internal API in several areas"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3885(para) 
msgid "Change WAL record CRCs from 64-bit to 32-bit (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3888(para) 
msgid "We determined that the extra cost of computing 64-bit CRCs was significant, and the gain in reliability too marginal to justify it."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3895(para) 
msgid "Prevent writing large empty gaps in WAL pages (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3901(para) 
msgid "Improve spinlock behavior on SMP machines, particularly Opterons (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3907(para) 
msgid "Allow nonconsecutive index columns to be used in a multicolumn index (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3911(para) 
msgid "For example, this allows an index on columns a,b,c to be used in a query with <command>WHERE a = 4 and c = 10</command>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3918(para) 
msgid "Skip WAL logging for <command>CREATE TABLE AS</command> / <command>SELECT INTO</command> (Simon)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3922(para) 
msgid "Since a crash during <command>CREATE TABLE AS</command> would cause the table to be dropped during recovery, there is no reason to WAL log as the table is loaded. (Logging still happens if WAL archiving is enabled, however.)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3931(para) 
msgid "Allow concurrent GiST index access (Teodor, Oleg)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3937(para) 
msgid "Add configuration parameter <varname>full_page_writes</varname> to control writing full pages to WAL (Bruce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3941(para) 
msgid "To prevent partial disk writes from corrupting the database, <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> writes a complete copy of each database disk page to WAL the first time it is modified after a checkpoint. This option turns off that functionality for more speed. This is safe to use with battery-backed disk caches where partial page writes cannot happen."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3952(para) 
msgid "Use <literal>O_DIRECT</literal> if available when using <literal>O_SYNC</literal> for <varname>wal_sync_method</varname> (Itagaki Takahiro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3957(para) 
msgid "<literal>O_DIRECT</literal> causes disk writes to bypass the kernel cache, and for WAL writes, this improves performance."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3964(para) 
msgid "Improve <command>COPY FROM</command> performance (Alon Goldshuv)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3967(para) 
msgid "This was accomplished by reading <command>COPY</command> input in larger chunks, rather than character by character."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3974(para) 
msgid "Improve the performance of <function>COUNT()</function>, <function>SUM</function>, <function>AVG()</function>, <function>STDDEV()</function>, and <function>VARIANCE()</function> (Neil, Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3985(title) 
msgid "Server Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3989(para) 
msgid "Prevent problems due to transaction ID (XID) wraparound (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:3992(para) 
msgid "The server will now warn when the transaction counter approaches the wraparound point. If the counter becomes too close to wraparound, the server will stop accepting queries. This ensures that data is not lost before needed vacuuming is performed."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4001(para) 
msgid "Fix problems with object IDs (OIDs) conflicting with existing system objects after the OID counter has wrapped around (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4008(para) 
msgid "Add warning about the need to increase <varname>max_fsm_relations</varname> and <varname>max_fsm_pages</varname> during <command>VACUUM</command> (Ron Mayer)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4016(para) 
msgid "Add <varname>temp_buffers</varname> configuration parameter to allow users to determine the size of the local buffer area for temporary table access (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4024(para) 
msgid "Add session start time and client IP address to <literal>pg_stat_activity</literal> (Magnus)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4031(para) 
msgid "Adjust <literal>pg_stat</literal> views for bitmap scans (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4034(para) 
msgid "The meanings of some of the fields have changed slightly."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4040(para) 
msgid "Enhance <literal>pg_locks</literal> view (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4046(para) 
msgid "Log queries for client-side <command>PREPARE</command> and <command>EXECUTE</command> (Simon)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4053(para) 
msgid "Allow Kerberos name and user name case sensitivity to be specified in <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> (Magnus)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4060(para) 
msgid "Add configuration parameter <varname>krb_server_hostname</varname> so that the server host name can be specified as part of service principal (Todd Kover)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4065(para) 
msgid "If not set, any service principal matching an entry in the keytab can be used. This is new Kerberos matching behavior in this release."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4073(para) 
msgid "Add <varname>log_line_prefix</varname> options for millisecond timestamps (<literal>%m</literal>) and remote host (<literal>%h</literal>) (Ed L.)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4081(para) 
msgid "Add WAL logging for GiST indexes (Teodor, Oleg)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4084(para) 
msgid "GiST indexes are now safe for crash and point-in-time recovery."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4090(para) 
msgid "Remove old <filename>*.backup</filename> files when we do <function>pg_stop_backup()</function> (Bruce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4094(para) 
msgid "This prevents a large number of <filename>*.backup</filename> files from existing in <filename>pg_xlog/</filename>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4101(para) 
msgid "Add configuration parameters to control TCP/IP keep-alive times for idle, interval, and count (Oliver Jowett)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4106(para) 
msgid "These values can be changed to allow more rapid detection of lost client connections."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4113(para) 
msgid "Add per-user and per-database connection limits (Petr Jelinek)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4116(para) 
msgid "Using <command>ALTER USER</command> and <command>ALTER DATABASE</command>, limits can now be enforced on the maximum number of sessions that can concurrently connect as a specific user or to a specific database. Setting the limit to zero disables user or database connections."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4125(para) 
msgid "Allow more than two gigabytes of shared memory and per-backend work memory on 64-bit machines (Koichi Suzuki)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4132(para) 
msgid "New system catalog <structname>pg_pltemplate</structname> allows overriding obsolete procedural-language definitions in dump files (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4143(title) 
msgid "Query Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4147(para) 
msgid "Add temporary views (Koju Iijima, Neil)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4153(para) 
msgid "Fix <command>HAVING</command> without any aggregate functions or <command>GROUP BY</command> so that the query returns a single group (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4157(para) 
msgid "Previously, such a case would treat the <command>HAVING</command> clause the same as a <command>WHERE</command> clause. This was not per spec."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4164(para) 
msgid "Add <command>USING</command> clause to allow additional tables to be specified to <command>DELETE</command> (Euler Taveira de Oliveira, Neil)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4168(para) 
msgid "In prior releases, there was no clear method for specifying additional tables to be used for joins in a <command>DELETE</command> statement. <command>UPDATE</command> already has a <literal>FROM</literal> clause for this purpose."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4177(para) 
msgid "Add support for <literal>\\x</literal> hex escapes in backend and ecpg strings (Bruce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4181(para) 
msgid "This is just like the standard C <literal>\\x</literal> escape syntax. Octal escapes were already supported."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4188(para) 
msgid "Add <command>BETWEEN SYMMETRIC</command> query syntax (Pavel Stehule)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4191(para) 
msgid "This feature allows <command>BETWEEN</command> comparisons without requiring the first value to be less than the second. For example, <command>2 BETWEEN [ASYMMETRIC] 3 AND 1</command> returns false, while <command>2 BETWEEN SYMMETRIC 3 AND 1</command> returns true. <command>BETWEEN ASYMMETRIC</command> was already supported."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4201(para) 
msgid "Add <command>NOWAIT</command> option to <command>SELECT ... FOR UPDATE/SHARE</command> (Hans-Juergen Schoenig)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4205(para) 
msgid "While the <varname>statement_timeout</varname> configuration parameter allows a query taking more than a certain amount of time to be canceled, the <command>NOWAIT</command> option allows a query to be canceled as soon as a <command>SELECT ... FOR UPDATE/SHARE</command> command cannot immediately acquire a row lock."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4218(title) 
msgid "Object Manipulation Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4222(para) 
msgid "Track dependencies of shared objects (Alvaro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4225(para) 
msgid "<productname>PostgreSQL</productname> allows global tables (users, databases, tablespaces) to reference information in multiple databases. This addition adds dependency information for global tables, so, for example, user ownership can be tracked across databases, so a user who owns something in any database can no longer be removed. Dependency tracking already existed for database-local objects."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4237(para) 
msgid "Allow limited <command>ALTER OWNER</command> commands to be performed by the object owner (Stephen Frost)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4241(para) 
msgid "Prior releases allowed only superusers to change object owners. Now, ownership can be transferred if the user executing the command owns the object and would be able to create it as the new owner (that is, the user is a member of the new owning role and that role has the CREATE permission that would be needed to create the object afresh)."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4252(para) 
msgid "Add <command>ALTER</command> object <command>SET SCHEMA</command> capability for some object types (tables, functions, types) (Bernd Helmle)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4256(para) 
msgid "This allows objects to be moved to different schemas."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4262(para) 
msgid "Add <command>ALTER TABLE ENABLE/DISABLE TRIGGER</command> to disable triggers (Satoshi Nagayasu)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4273(title) 
msgid "Utility Command Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4277(para) 
msgid "Allow <command>TRUNCATE</command> to truncate multiple tables in a single command (Alvaro)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4281(para) 
msgid "Because of referential integrity checks, it is not allowed to truncate a table that is part of a referential integrity constraint. Using this new functionality, <command>TRUNCATE</command> can be used to truncate such tables, if both tables involved in a referential integrity constraint are truncated in a single <command>TRUNCATE</command> command."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4292(para) 
msgid "Properly process carriage returns and line feeds in <command>COPY CSV</command> mode (Andrew)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4296(para) 
msgid "In release 8.0, carriage returns and line feeds in <command>CSV COPY TO</command> were processed in an inconsistent manner. (This was documented on the TODO list.)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4304(para) 
msgid "Add <command>COPY WITH CSV HEADER</command> to allow a header line as the first line in <command>COPY</command> (Andrew)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4308(para) 
msgid "This allows handling of the common <command>CSV</command> usage of placing the column names on the first line of the data file. For <command>COPY TO</command>, the first line contains the column names, and for <command>COPY FROM</command>, the first line is ignored."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4317(para) 
msgid "On Windows, display better sub-second precision in <command>EXPLAIN ANALYZE</command> (Magnus)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4324(para) 
msgid "Add trigger duration display to <command>EXPLAIN ANALYZE</command> (Tom)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4328(para) 
msgid "Prior releases included trigger execution time as part of the total execution time, but did not show it separately. It is now possible to see how much time is spent in each trigger."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4336(para) 
msgid "Add support for <literal>\\x</literal> hex escapes in <command>COPY</command> (Sergey Ten)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4340(para) 
msgid "Previous releases only supported octal escapes."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4346(para) 
msgid "Make <command>SHOW ALL</command> include variable descriptions (Matthias Schmidt)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4350(para) 
msgid "<command>SHOW</command> varname still only displays the variable's value and does not include the description."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4357(para) 
msgid "Make <application>initdb</application> create a new standard database called <literal>postgres</literal>, and convert utilities to use <literal>postgres</literal> rather than <literal>template1</literal> for standard lookups (Dave)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4363(para) 
msgid "In prior releases, <literal>template1</literal> was used both as a default connection for utilities like <application>createuser</application>, and as a template for new databases. This caused <command>CREATE DATABASE</command> to sometimes fail, because a new database cannot be created if anyone else is in the template database. With this change, the default connection database is now <literal>postgres</literal>, meaning it is much less likely someone will be using <literal>template1</literal> during <command>CREATE DATABASE</command>."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4377(para) 
msgid "Create new <application>reindexdb</application> command-line utility by moving <filename>/contrib/reindexdb</filename> into the server (Euler Taveira de Oliveira)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4389(title) 
msgid "Data Type and Function Changes"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4393(para) 
msgid "Add <function>MAX()</function> and <function>MIN()</function> aggregates for array types (Koju Iijima)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4400(para) 
msgid "Fix <function>to_date()</function> and <function>to_timestamp()</function> to behave reasonably when <literal>CC</literal> and <literal>YY</literal> fields are both used (Karel Zak)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4405(para) 
msgid "If the format specification contains <literal>CC</literal> and a year specification is <literal>YYY</literal> or longer, ignore the <literal>CC</literal>. If the year specification is <literal>YY</literal> or shorter, interpret <literal>CC</literal> as the previous century."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4414(para) 
msgid "Add <function>md5(bytea)</function> (Abhijit Menon-Sen)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4417(para) 
msgid "<function>md5(text)</function> already existed."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4423(para) 
msgid "Add support for <command>numeric ^ numeric</command> based on <function>power(numeric, numeric)</function>"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4427(para) 
msgid "The function already existed, but there was no operator assigned to it."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4434(para) 
msgid "Fix <type>NUMERIC</type> modulus by properly truncating the quotient during computation (Bruce)"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-RtQO/release-8.1.xml:4438(para) 
