msgid "<command>OUT</command> is an alternate way for a function to return values. Instead of using <command>RETURN</command>, values can be returned by assigning to parameters declared as <command>OUT</command> or <command>INOUT</command>. This is notationally simpler in some cases, particularly so when multiple values need to be returned. While returning multiple values from a function was possible in previous releases, this greatly simplifies the process. (The feature will be extended to other server-side languages in future releases.)"
